<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,461,822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
There is no register of a 
<typeStatus box="[531,581,602,628]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
specimen (or any other material) of 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1355,602,627]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Calyptranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rostellata">
<emphasis box="[1063,1355,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Calyptranthes rostellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in C; nevertheless, Miers' collection in BM matches the protologue and is very possibly an isotype of the species. It is easy to understand the difficulties that Mattos and Legrand faced in assigning this curious species to a genus, because solitary and calyptrate flowers were generally assigned to either 
<taxonomicName box="[1094,1260,719,744]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Calyptranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1094,1260,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Calyptranthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1429,719,744]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Mitranthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1300,1429,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Mitranthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was not until 1984 that 
<bibRefCitation author="Landrum, L. R." box="[491,701,757,783]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="161 - 166" refId="ref6831" refString="Landrum, L. R. (1984) Taxonomic implications of the discovery of calyptrate species of Myrceugenia (Myrtaceae). Brittonia 36: 161 - 166." type="journal article" year="1984">Landrum (1984)</bibRefCitation>
showed that such a suite of characters is also present in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,304,796,821]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrceugenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,304,796,821]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Myrceugenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
